.com/amazon-hardware-event-2023-liveblog-live-updates-on-new-devices-and-services-140009216.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 63f0c650-e775-41f8-a575-d35e8d8b6129</guid><dc:creator>比利·斯蒂尔</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 20 Sep 2023 14:00:09 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1695046863</ingested><modified> 2023-09-18T14:21:07+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Billy Steele]]></category><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/56c5c4f0-562e-11ee-bf77-cd9171fd9464" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/56c5c4f0-562e-11ee-bf77-cd9171fd9464" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Lucas Jackson/Amazon]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Amazon HQ2]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Amazon HQ2]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Twelve South’s HiRise Pro is a slick height-adjustable laptop stand]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>我已经尝试在家工作的设置几个月了，但仍然没有达到我想要的效果。我尝试过站立式办公桌、中世纪的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.google.com/search?q=mid-century+bureau&amp;newwindow=1&amp;rlz=1C5GCEA_enGB1063GB1064&amp;sxsrf=AB5stBiB_82ABOYNRQ4Mwhtco9xq7k-Ffg%3A1688988180001&amp;ei=E-qrZMzEPPrd7_UP24ifmAk&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiMmv6jg4SAAxX67rsIHVvEB5MQ4dUDCA8&amp;uact=5&amp;oq=mid-century+bureau&amp;gs_lcp=Cgxnd3Mtd2l6LXNlcnAQAzIECCMQJzIGCAAQFhAeMgYIABAWEB4yBggAEBYQHjIGCAAQFhAeMgYIABAWEB4yBggAEBYQHjIGCAAQFhAeMgYIABAWEB4yBggAEBYQHjoKCAAQRxDWBBCwA0oECEEYAFCBAliBAmDJA2gBcAF4AIABgwGIAYMBkgEDMC4xmAEAoAEBwAEByAEI&amp;sclient=gws-wiz-serp">办公桌</a>（不是开玩笑），还有真正支撑我背部的椅子，但有时正是一些小东西让整个设置发挥作用，比如十二南的第一个高度可调的 MacBook 支架， <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy50d2VsdmVzb3V0aC5jb20vcHJvZHVjdHMvaGlyaXNlLXByby1mb3ItbWFjYm9vayIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjBjMGNhNTMtNTUxNS00YWViLWFjZTYtNGI1YjhmZDAyOTZkIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAXzjWEStbHfZtTi7UWtjcyGwUUFLouuozBcNpcNHf1xJ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twelvesouth.com%2Fproducts%2Fhirise-pro-for-macbook" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.twelvesouth.com/products/hirise-pro-for-macbook">HiRise Pro。</a></p><p>十二南长期以来一直为 Apple 的几乎所有产品生产优质、时尚的外设、保护壳等。这款后续支架与所有 MacBook（和其他笔记本电脑）兼容，在保持坚固的同时增加了屏幕高度的一定程度的可调节性，它甚至包括 MagSafe 充电平台 - 尽管您必须提供自己的 MagSafe 充电盘。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/c343eac0-50a8-11ee-bfbf-2d6d8eef943d" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/c343eac0-50a8-11ee-bfbf-2d6d8eef943d" style="height:2400px;width:3600px;" alt="十二 SouthHiRise Pro 评论" data-uuid="9be6687a-15ae-39d3-84e5-1959888e5d1e"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Mat Smith / Engadget</div></figure><p>这是一个坚固、优质的支架，在办公室或在家工作的环境中不会显得格格不入。该公司一直致力于打造与 Apple 美学完美契合的配件，包括精致的细节、拉丝金属饰面和简约的设计。我想没人想要一个华丽的笔记本电脑支架吧？ V 形支架部分采用橡胶表面处理，可抓住笔记本电脑的底座，而 MagSafe 充电区域则采用光滑的纯素皮革表面。</p><p> HiRise Pro 可以将您的屏幕抬高到距办公桌六英寸的位置，将笔记本电脑屏幕移至您的视线范围内。如果需要，可以使用金属螺钉将其调节至较低水平。十二南相信 HiRise Pro 的最大高度可确保任何笔记本电脑网络摄像头都处于理想高度。我喜欢的——也是我一直在寻找的——是一种改善笔记本电脑工作人体工程学的简单方法。我不想要一个更大的显示器，总是安装在眼睛的高度——即使我<em>应该这样做</em>。如果您已经有第二个屏幕和显示器，那么如果您对美观要求特别高，那么这个支架意味着您可以将笔记本电脑屏幕与任何外部显示器对齐。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/c3574bb0-50a8-11ee-97f8-f649168d218d" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/c3574bb0-50a8-11ee-97f8-f649168d218d" style="height:2400px;width:3600px;" alt="十二 SouthHiRise Pro 评论" data-uuid="53bc2db0-e45b-3780-acd8-3086038166cb"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Mat Smith / Engadget</div></figure><p>这感觉就像是让站立式办公桌为我工作所需要的最后一件事。我现在还在用<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-tripod-desk-pro-is-a-portable-standing-desk-that-upgraded-my-wfh-setup-150037026.htm">这个三脚架办公桌</a>，视线已经<em>差不多</em>了。老实说，我会受益于 HiRise Pro 增加一两英寸的高度，但十二南可能已经达到了稳定性极限。</p><p>使用这种笔记本电脑支架，您实际上无法使用内置触控板或键盘，这一点需要记住。您需要投资无线或有线替代品。最重要的是，虽然它的价格并不离谱，但对于一个已经有 40 美元替代品的摊位来说，100 美元已经是很多了。其中之一是 Twelve South 最近推出的<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy50d2VsdmVzb3V0aC5jb20vcHJvZHVjdHMvY3VydmUtc2UiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjIwYzBjYTUzLTU1MTUtNGFlYi1hY2U2LTRiNWI4ZmQwMjk2ZCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAc-X-4QvJdgyFqmeOtV6b-9eklswyEIzFthzSHmM_SPq&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twelvesouth.com%2Fproducts%2Fcurve-se" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.twelvesouth.com/products/curve-se">Curve SE 笔记本电脑支架</a>。</p><p>在此之前，我在一个基本但笨重的宜家架子（你可以在我的一些<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-tripod-desk-pro-is-a-portable-standing-desk-that-upgraded-my-wfh-setup-150037026.html">评论</a>中看到它）和一个可折叠的便携式笔记本电脑支架之间进行交换，该支架不能完全将设备从表面上抬起，但至少可以将其向上倾斜。它还配备了大量端口，甚至还有一个 SD 卡读卡器。我对十二南在未来的笔记本电脑支架上塞进更多东西很感兴趣——它在 Mac 外围设备上做了更多的事情，所以为什么不在这里呢？也许该公司正在等待推出 HiRise Max？但愿如此。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/twelve-souths-hirise-pro-is-a-slick-height-adjustable-laptop-stand-130027673.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/twelve-souths-hirise-pro-is-a-slick-height-adjustable-laptop-stand-130027673.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 20c0ca53-5515-4aeb-ace6-4b5b8fd0296d</guid><dc:creator>马特·史密斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 20 Sep 2023 13:30:27 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1695217251</ingested><modified> 2023-09-20T13:40:55+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Computing]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mat Smith]]></category><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/11718fe0-57bb-11ee-bdb7-94057b087f80" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/11718fe0-57bb-11ee-bdb7-94057b087f80" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Mat Smith / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Twelve South’s HiRise Pro laptop stand seen with a laptop on it in a normal desktop setup with keyboard, touchpad and a tiki-style mug.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Twelve South’s HiRise Pro]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Apple Watch Series 9 review: Freedom from touching your screen]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>您是否看过<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://shutupandtakemymoney.com/girls-hands-be-like-meme/">关于</a>人们无缘无故地在手指上<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://img.ifunny.co/images/e309863b8a92cd44c511678ff76bdf86751e8127978dddfdc7c108de0fba6138_1.webp">悬挂太多东西的</a>模因？我并不自豪地承认这一点，但我就是其中之一。无论我携带多大的包，我总是发现我的双手很满，这使得我很难在旅途中与手机或智能手表进行交互。我并不孤单。这就是为什么语音控制助手和免提手势如此吸引人。</p><p>通过<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0FwcGxlLVNtYXJ0d2F0Y2gtQWx1bWludW0tRml0bmVzcy1UcmFja2VyL2RwL0IwQ0hYMVJWTVQvP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTRuZy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiZjBiMjA5MTEtZGFlOS00MTM4LTgxODktMmMzMTdmZGRiNjY5In0&amp;signature=AQAAAQ6m2F2hIx3FPnDh7uAXRjypKvhWC-a1ju0oH7kbAnkC&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FApple-Smartwatch-Aluminum-Fitness-Tracker%2Fdp%2FB0CHX1RVMT%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/Apple-Smartwatch-Aluminum-Fitness-Tracker/dp/B0CHX1RVMT/">Apple Watch Series 9</a> ，该公司推出了两种新的交互方式：双击和抬起说话（对 Siri）。它还推出了设备上的 Siri 处理功能，让你可以向助手询问你的健康数据并记录你的每日统计数据。这些功能是由为该设备供电的新 S9 系统级封装 (SiP) 实现的，这意味着它们可能无法通过 watchOS 10 提供给旧型号。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p><core-commerce id="5574308bc31440c0970d1cf2e1c9eb8e" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-watch-ultra-2-and-series-9-first-impressions-double-tap-is-accurate-and-tricky-203116431.html">Series 9</a>还配备了新的第二代超宽带 (UWB) 芯片，就像 iPhone 15 系列中的芯片一样，它允许在 ping 配对手机时更新界面。从外观上看，新的 Apple Watch 看起来和它的前身没什么两样，但光是新的手势就足以吸引一些人今年升级。</p><h2>双击</h2><p>全面披露：由于一系列 FedEx 事故，直到昨天我才收到启用了 Double Tap 功能的 Apple Watch 的单独样品。这意味着我只花了大约一天的时间在现实世界中测试新手势。需要明确的是，该功能不会在 9 月 22 日发货的手表上提供，并将在 10 月晚些时候通过无线方式激活。<em>除了将提供给消费者的实际设备外</em>，苹果还向审阅者发送了启用了 Double Tap 的补充设备，用于我们的报道和测试目的。不过，不用担心，这篇评论的其余部分是基于我自上周苹果发布会以来使用的 Series 9。这只是我迟到的 Double Tap 样本。尽管如此，我已经对它何时以及如何有用有了更好的认识。</p><p></p><p>当双手，或者至少是我的手表手都被占用时，双击显然没有帮助。您至少需要有拇指和食指可以捏住。但当我打扫公寓、拿着侧板、举起一个哑铃或读书时，这个动作确实让我的生活变得更轻松。事实上，我喜欢它只是因为我可以继续用右手在手机上滚动 Reddit，而不必放下设备来滑动左手腕上的东西。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca73f450-5749-11ee-af9f-489b428a2786" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca73f450-5749-11ee-af9f-489b428a2786" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Apple Watch Series 9 戴在人的手腕上，手放在蓝白色的轨道上。" data-uuid="2fa837ef-4237-38c5-96aa-3affd959ef91"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Cherlynn Low / Engadget</div></figure><p> Series 9 相当擅长识别我何时快速捏了两次，但我花了几次尝试才找到正确的节奏。你不能敲得太快或太微妙，否则它不会注册。我讨厌公司告诉我们做错了什么，但在我们正在学习一种新姿势的情况下，我倾向于投入工作。</p><p>苹果结合使用加速计、陀螺仪和光学心率监测器的数据来检测运动和血流变化。这可以让手表了解您触摸中指和指针时的区别。我可以通过假装打响拇指和食指来触发“双击”，也可以在敲击手指侧面而不是触摸板时触发。</p><p>这也是澄清 Double Tap 与<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apples-sign-time-brings-up-a-sign-language-translator-on-demand-172828126.html">2021 年 watchOS 中引入的</a>Assistive Touch 有很大不同的好时机。后者是一项<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/accessibility-in-tech-2021-report-card-apple-google-microsoft-amazon-facebook-meta-twitter-210034415.html">注重辅助功能的功能</a>， <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2011-07-11-apple-enables-assistive-touch-features-on-ipad-in-latest-ios-5.html">多年来已在 iOS 中提供</a>，并允许具有不同移动需求的用户与各自的操作系统进行交互。您必须首先进入设置才能在手表上启用它，然后您可以<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3N1cHBvcnQuYXBwbGUuY29tL2d1aWRlL3dhdGNoL2Fzc2lzdGl2ZXRvdWNoLWFwZGVjNzBiZmQyZC93YXRjaG9zIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJmMGIyMDkxMS1kYWU5LTQxMzgtODE4OS0yYzMxN2ZkZGI2NjkifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAT07EpJD7wqd0R3oi0S-MywFv81loGA75VNxCUD5w5vc&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.apple.com%2Fguide%2Fwatch%2Fassistivetouch-apdec70bfd2d%2Fwatchos" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://support.apple.com/guide/watch/assistivetouch-apdec70bfd2d/watchos">使用捏合和握紧等手势进行导航</a>。握紧两次将激活辅助触摸，从而在屏幕上显示项目周围的轮廓。然后，捏捏将在各个元素之间移动，握紧将起到敲击它们的作用。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca704ad0-5749-11ee-beae-3fed3912d496" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca704ad0-5749-11ee-beae-3fed3912d496" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Apple Watch Series 9 悬浮在手腕上，屏幕上显示 Smart Stack。" data-uuid="4e9d0c1f-52e1-3b8e-9c7a-418e26ddd4c1"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Cherlynn Low / Engadget</div></figure><p>辅助触摸比 Double Tap 更完整、更细致，因为它可以帮助用户访问所有 watchOS。同时，新功能更多的是为了方便，而且只有一个操作可用。它还做了非常具体的事情。您首先必须确保 Series 9 已唤醒。在主屏幕上，双击可拉出智能堆栈，随后的捏合可滚动浏览该页面上的小部件。您可以更改默认设置，以便后续双击智能堆栈会进入顶部卡片。</p><p>在 watchOS 的其他地方，双击将触发主按钮。例如，启动或暂停计时器、暂停闹钟、播放音乐或回复消息。苹果公司也对其中一些应用程序进行了深思熟虑的编程。如果您使用“双击”来回复消息，则会弹出语音输入选项，以便您可以口述回复。这是一个很好的触摸，考虑到如果你已经捏着手指对通知做出反应，你可能无法用另一只手敲出消息。</p><p>但 Double Tap 并非在 watchOS 的每个部分都可用。例如，当我查看“电话”应用程序或“移动”铃声时，该手势没有执行任何操作。一个小指示器似乎表明它确实注册了；它只是没有将操作映射到页面上的任何内容。顺便说一下，我喜欢这个小指示器气泡，因为它对帮助我学习手势有很大帮助。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca741b60-5749-11ee-bfff-96fc8a455d70" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca741b60-5749-11ee-bfff-96fc8a455d70" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Apple Watch Series 9 戴在一个人的手腕上，背景中手拿着一个黑色水瓶。屏幕上显示正念应用程序。" data-uuid="abbb79e3-eb78-36cf-b1c4-c846acef7d34"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Cherlynn Low / Engadget</div></figure><p>话虽如此，感觉 Double Tap 可能并不像主题演讲中看起来的那样具有开创性。但它仍然是一个有用的工具，可能会减少我抬起手腕和滑动屏幕的需要。</p><h2>更好的 Siri</h2><p> Apple 减少我对 Series 9 显示屏依赖的另一种方法是通过语音控制。具体来说，新手表（包括 Ultra 2）上的 Siri 请求将在设备上处理。这样做有很多好处——响应速度是最不重要的。我并排比较了 Series 9 和 Series 8，今年的手表在响应我的“Hey Siri”请求方面仅稍快一些。</p><p>设备上处理的其他优势更具影响力。例如，在离线或与 iPhone 断开连接时仍然可以向 Siri 寻求帮助，这是一个令人惊讶的简单升级。当我去健身房时，我把配对的 iPhone 15 Pro 留在家里，当我回家时仍然可以告诉助手记录一次户外散步时，我松了口气（因为我的双手像往常一样忙）。</p><p>由于您的请求不再离开手表，Apple 还可以让您向 Siri 询问您的健康数据。您可以询问助理您睡了多长时间、当天走了多少步或记录经期等。其中一些现已推出，而另一些则将在今年晚些时候的软件更新中提供。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca741b60-5749-11ee-b6ff-e0a63e1154f6" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca741b60-5749-11ee-b6ff-e0a63e1154f6" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Apple Watch Series 9 佩戴在某些健身器材前的手腕上，显示 Move 环应用程序的“锻炼”页面。" data-uuid="f1dd02dd-7c4f-31d1-b825-5425df151cff"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Cherlynn Low / Engadget</div></figure><p>目前，反响并不好。我让 Siri 告诉我走了多少步或消耗了多少卡路里，它并没有给我直接答案，而是将我带到“移动”或“锻炼”环页面。我询问了我的心率，并被带到心率应用程序进行读数，这是合理的。但希望通过软件更新，我能得到关于步数或卡路里的直接答案。</p><p>由于我还无法对其进行测试，因此我无法完全评估 Siri 健康请求的影响力，但我怀疑这将使苹果领先于其智能手表竞争对手。仅用声音编辑统计数据可以让人们更轻松地输入数据，这最终将改善您从手表获得的见解。目前还没有其他可穿戴操作系统提供此功能。</p><p>最后，在 Series 9 中，苹果还添加了“举起说话”功能。从理论上讲，这意味着您应该能够将手表放在嘴边并向 Siri 询问事情。但根据我的经验，这几乎没有一半的时间有效。我希望它更加一致，因为，请原谅我在这里的夸张，当它确实按预期运行时，感觉几乎是神奇的。我抬起手腕，对着表壳说话，Siri 图标就会出现，还有我刚才说的话。不再需要长时间按下数字表冠或说“嘿 Siri”。</p><p>好消息是，即使“抬起说话”功能没有注册，我仍然可以回去说“嘿 Siri”。尝试测试这个功能真的很烦人，因为我很快就因为重复的手腕抬起而感到疲倦。听着，这是在健身房锻炼手臂的一周，好吗？ </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca74deb0-5749-11ee-bf4f-faaf3d02f46f" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca74deb0-5749-11ee-bf4f-faaf3d02f46f" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="绿叶前的 Apple Watch Series 9 佩戴在手腕上，显示户外步行锻炼的摘要。" data-uuid="bbddee17-0274-3081-8eed-5791ced5c4f9"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Cherlynn Low / Engadget</div></figure><h2> UWB 精确定位、使用情况和电池寿命</h2><p>Series 9 上最后一项与硬件相关的功能是其第二代 UWB 芯片，它支持新的界面来定位配对的 iPhone。目前，您所能做的就是使用 Apple Watch 来 ping 手机并使其响铃。将 Series 9 与另一台配备新型 UWB 芯片的设备配对后，您不仅可以准确地看到您距离放错位置的设备有多少英尺，还可以看到它的方向。</p><p>在旧金山机场通过安检后，我几乎惊慌失措，当时我以为我丢失了 iPhone 15 Pro Max。值得庆幸的是，我当时头脑清醒，并使用 Series 9 拨通了电话。听到铃声我感到非常轻松，但当手表告诉我我距离听筒只有一英尺半时，我也感到很有趣。</p><p>要查看告诉您丢失物品所在方向的新界面，您必须距离它超过五英尺。我从健身房回到家，使用 Series 9 来查看 iPhone 的位置，屏幕上的弧线和距离指示器可以轻松引导我到我离开的沙发上。当我到达五英尺以内时，电话嗡嗡作响，这有助于找到它。</p><p>我没有 HomePod 来测试这一点，但 Series 9 也会知道您何时在距离 4 米之内，并自动拉出“正在播放”屏幕，以便您可以快速控制播放。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca749091-5749-11ee-adfa-00f70597097b" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca749091-5749-11ee-adfa-00f70597097b" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Apple Watch Series 9 悬在手腕上，显示主屏幕，阳光从数字表冠上反射出来。" data-uuid="66c6e01b-8056-33e5-9bd3-88ac1a213dd4"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Cherlynn Low / Engadget</div></figure><p>如果您的 Series 8（或更旧型号）在阳光下有点太暗，或者在昏暗的卧室里太亮，您可能会喜欢新型号的屏幕现在可以达到 2,000 尼特和低至 1 尼特。这是 Series 8 亮度的两倍，我在阅读时从来没有遇到过困难，所以我发现最新型号在晴朗的日子里也很容易看清，这是有道理的。</p><p>但值得注意的是，在黑暗的房间里，低尼特显示屏可能会让一些人难以阅读。我同时佩戴了 Series 8 和 Series 9，新款手表明显变暗，对比度低的较小文字几乎难以辨认。如果这影响到您，好消息是您仍然可以调整一般设备亮度，以避免屏幕变暗。</p><p> Series 9 没有什么太大的不同，你无法通过更新到 watchOS 10 来获得。也就是说，除非你非常喜欢新的粉色选项，以至于你愿意为此购买一个全新的设备（我会理解，因为我喜欢我的评论单元的粉红色）。最新的硬件将为您带来 S9 SiP，它处理机器学习任务的速度比上一代快两倍，同时能效提高 25%。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca741b61-5749-11ee-8dcf-c70672c173ba" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca741b61-5749-11ee-8dcf-c70672c173ba" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Apple Watch Series 9 戴在一个人的手腕上，背景中手拿着一个黑色水瓶。屏幕显示功能性力量训练锻炼的摘要。" data-uuid="93e61cba-b0d7-3e92-a4e5-25509f4aa471"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Cherlynn Low / Engadget</div></figure><p>老实说，我几乎没有注意到性能上的差异，而且电池寿命感觉有点短，Series 9 每天晚上都需要充电，而不是每晚。我认为这是因为我收到的评测设备是较小的 41 毫米尺寸，而我一直使用的 Series 8 是较大的 44 毫米版本，并且可以理解的是它具有更持久的电池。苹果表示，Series 9 的续航时间仍为 18 小时，尽管这与前几代产品一致，但我希望它能持续更长时间。三星和 Fitbit 的智能手表通常可以运行两天或更长的时间，很高兴看到苹果给我们更多的时间。</p><p> watchOS 10 也带来了很多变化，但由于使用较旧 Apple Watch 的用户也可以使用这些变化，因此我不会在这里介绍它们。我也不会深入研究我们已经测试过的东西，比如健身和睡眠跟踪或跌倒检测和紧急求救。它们不会影响您是否购买新手表的决定。</p><p>无论您拥有哪一代手表，您都可以使用另一件新东西：FineWoven 表带。这是苹果公司的皮革替代品，苹果公司<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-is-removing-leather-from-all-its-products-for-environmental-reasons-173559661.html">宣布将停止销售皮革</a>，以减少碳足迹。 FineWoven 是一种由回收材料制成的类似绒面革的材料，旨在提供优质的感觉。我不介意，虽然我更喜欢皮革的质感，但为了拯救我们的环境，我很乐意放弃良好的触感。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca7098f1-5749-11ee-8e8f-747ee291257a" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ca7098f1-5749-11ee-8e8f-747ee291257a" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Apple Watch Series 9 佩戴在半空中的手腕上，模糊的背景中有一些气球。" data-uuid="827a288b-c0fe-3c74-b527-5a86a25d3164"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Cherlynn Low / Engadget</div></figure><h2>包起来</h2><p><a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0FwcGxlLVNtYXJ0d2F0Y2gtQWx1bWludW0tRml0bmVzcy1UcmFja2VyL2RwL0IwQ0hYMVJWTVQvP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTRuZy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiZjBiMjA5MTEtZGFlOS00MTM4LTgxODktMmMzMTdmZGRiNjY5In0&amp;signature=AQAAAQ6m2F2hIx3FPnDh7uAXRjypKvhWC-a1ju0oH7kbAnkC&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FApple-Smartwatch-Aluminum-Fitness-Tracker%2Fdp%2FB0CHX1RVMT%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/Apple-Smartwatch-Aluminum-Fitness-Tracker/dp/B0CHX1RVMT/">Apple Watch Series 9</a>和 Ultra 2 是该公司首款碳中和产品，这是一项值得称赞的重大成就。我们必须赞扬苹果公司努力将其对地球的不利影响降到最低，尽管它在营销上大肆宣传（事实上，它在一场希望人们购买的新设备发布会上讽刺地概述了其 2030 年愿景）。</p><p>例如，如果你有环保意识，该公司在净碳中和方面的努力可能会影响你是否购买Apple Watch Series 9，而不是Fitbit等竞争对手的产品。但如果这不是您的首要任务，那么您更有可能根据 Double Tap 和 Siri 等功能以及性能和电池寿命来做出决定。</p><p> Series 9 是一款功能强大、功能全面的智能手表，仍然是同类产品中最好的。仅双击和设备上的 Siri 就足以让你以旧换新 Apple Watch（是的，甚至是 Series 8），尤其是如果你讨厌滑动或点击手腕上的小屏幕的话。</p><p>更让我感兴趣的是开始成形的未来愿景。凭借双击等手势和对语音命令的更加关注，以及今年早些时候推出的 Vision Pro 耳机，很明显苹果已经为未来几年制定了方向。我很好奇可穿戴设备的定位，并且我强烈怀疑 Series 9 只是为未来更加身临其境的免提生态系统奠定了基础。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/apple-watch-series-9-review-freedom-from-touching-your-screen-130009764.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/apple-watch-series-9-review-freedom-from-touching-your-screen-130009764.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> f0b20911-dae9-4138-8189-2c317fddb669</guid><dc:creator>彻林·洛</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 20 Sep 2023 13:00:09 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1695215755</ingested><modified> 2023-09-20T13:16:05+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Cherlynn Low]]></category><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/a4fc4790-5749-11ee-8fb2-b86b1385cef0" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/a4fc4790-5749-11ee-8fb2-b86b1385cef0" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Cherlynn Low / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[The Apple Watch Series 9 on a person's wrist.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Apple Watch Series 9]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best smart speakers for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>语音助手现在无处不在——在你的手机上、你的电视上，甚至可能在你的厨房用具上。但人们与 Siri、Alexa 和 Google Assistant 互动的最常见方式之一是通过智能扬声器，而且现在有各种不同价位的此类设备。拥有始终监听唤醒词的智能家居设备也有缺点，因为向亚马逊、苹果和谷歌提供更多个人信息可能是一个值得怀疑的决定。也就是说，所有这些公司都让管理数据的使用方式变得更加容易——你可以选择不让人工审查你的一些语音查询，而且使用各种数字助理来管理和删除你的历史记录也更简单。</p><p>好消息是，现在是购买智能扬声器的最佳时机，特别是如果您是音乐迷。尽管有很多好处，最初的 Amazon Echo 和 Google Home 设备听起来并不好。另一方面，Sonos 制造了音质出色的 WiFi 连接扬声器，但缺乏任何语音控制智能功能。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>现在一切都变了。 Sonos 于 2022 年发布了自己的语音助手，并在其最新的扬声器上支持 Alexa。与此同时，谷歌和亚马逊通过最新的扬声器在音质方面取得了巨大的进步。即使是像 Echo Dot 和 Nest Mini 这样的低端型号听起来也比早期版本要好得多。随着这些扬声器的日益普及，现在有比以往更多的选择。让我们来看看我们精选的不同价位和不同用途的最佳智能扬声器。</p><h2>挑选助理</h2><p>大多数人应该做的第一件事是决定他们想要使用什么语音助手。 Google Assistant 和亚马逊的 Alexa 都是得到良好支持的选项，并且不断发展，新功能不断添加。几年前，Alexa 与更多的智能家居设备配合使用，但目前，基本上任何值得购买的智能设备都可以同时使用这两种设备。</p><p>这主要是个人喜好的问题。如果您已经在 Android 手机上使用 Google Assistant，那么坚持使用 Google Assistant 是有意义的。不过，虽然 Alexa 不太擅长回答常识性问题，但它可以很好地与 Google 帐户中的日历等内容同步。它也可以与最广泛的智能家居设备配合使用。如果您从未使用过<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL2FwcHMuYXBwbGUuY29tL3VzL2FwcC9hbWF6b24tYWxleGEvaWQ5NDQwMTE2MjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjIyZTNmMGI3LWMxNzktMzkyYS04MjFjLWU2ZGY1M2MyODBhNiJ9&amp;signature=AQAAARYWVaYBWoXE3saOh9reSP5jBvl5JqgaMir5u_WYF0GM&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fapps.apple.com%2Fus%2Fapp%2Famazon-alexa%2Fid944011620">Alexa</a>或<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3BsYXkuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS9zdG9yZS9hcHBzL2RldGFpbHM_aWQ9Y29tLmdvb2dsZS5hbmRyb2lkLmFwcHMuZ29vZ2xlYXNzaXN0YW50JmhsPWVuX1VTJmdsPVVTIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIyMmUzZjBiNy1jMTc5LTM5MmEtODIxYy1lNmRmNTNjMjgwYTYifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAdocdFrFh3jxXbyI2jt8pzj7IYj1eQKc51OO9U0yOHE0&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fplay.google.com%2Fstore%2Fapps%2Fdetails%3Fid%3Dcom.google.android.apps.googleassistant%26hl%3Den_US%26gl%3DUS">Google Assistant</a> ，您可以将它们的应用程序下载到您的智能手机上，并在购买扬声器之前花一些时间进行测试。</p><p>如果您购买带有麦克风的 Sonos 设备，您还可以使用<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sonos-voice-control-assistant-for-music-200538441.html">该公司自己的语音助手</a>，由 Giancarlo Esposito 配音。它纯粹专注于音乐控制，因此您不会用它来执行发送消息或询问天气预报等操作。但作为音乐助手，Sonos 语音控制通常相当快速且可靠。</p><p>至于 Apple，您不会惊讶地发现 HomePod 和 HomePod mini 是市场上唯一兼容 Siri 的扬声器。苹果的 Siri 因不如 Alexa 或 Google Assistant 智能而闻名，但它完全能够处理常见的语音查询，例如回答问题、控制智能家居设备、发送消息、拨打电话和流媒体音乐。从技术上讲，Siri 和苹果的 HomeKit 技术并不像竞争对手那样适用于那么多智能家居设备，但找到兼容的设备并不难。在过去的几年里，苹果无疑改进了 Siri 的功能，提供了方便的功能，例如利用 HomePod 和 HomePod Mini 中内置温度传感器的对讲工具和例程。</p><h2> 50 美元以下最佳智能音箱：Amazon Echo Dot </h2><p><core-commerce id="d9b8d32fabd14ba39688ca99f80af4ce" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>大多数人进入智能音箱世界的切入点都不会是昂贵的设备。亚马逊的第四代<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlCOFYxTFozP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWQ2LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIyMmUzZjBiNy1jMTc5LTM5MmEtODIxYy1lNmRmNTNjMjgwYTYifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAZXNEHk7FsGNE_XvtNGqcNRKg4X5smBOvwFOgWVpzaOU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09B8V1LZ3%3F">Echo Dot</a>和谷歌的<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Walmart;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=3719d8d4-5edd-4817-998a-91f3229e7323&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Walmart&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWI09cTB1paP_8rNk0Y7QX-pWjYPXnnM13p5n65pcwPv&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2FGoogle-Nest-Mini-2nd-Generation-Chalk%2F751612012">Nest Mini</a>是最明显的起点，有两个重要原因。第一，它们很便宜：Nest Mini 和 Echo Dost 的售价都是 50 美元。二是他们有能力。尽管价格低廉，这些扬声器实际上可以完成与更大、更昂贵的设备相同的功能。</p><p> Google Nest Mini 于 2019 年底发布，但亚马逊去年刚刚更新了 Echo Dot。对于大多数人来说，Echo Dot 是最好的小型智能扬声器。亚马逊不断改进其 Echo 设备系列的音频性能，Echo Dot 也不例外。它产生的声音比我对 50 美元扬声器的预期要响亮、清晰得多。 Nest Mini 听起来不错，非常适合在卧室里聆听，同时为新的一天做好准备，但 Echo Dot 是一款更好的通用音乐聆听设备。</p><p>从设计角度来看，亚马逊推出了最新的 Echo Dot，打破了常规。新款 Dot 的形状像一个小地球仪，而不是像 Nest Mini 那样的小冰球。它比 Nest Mini 大得多，但这样的尺寸为它提供了容纳高端音频组件的空间。虽然大部分情况下是免提的，但 Dot 将物理音量按钮和静音开关保留在顶部，以及一个用于激活 Alexa 语音控制的按钮。虽然 Dot 看起来不像 Nest Mini 那样时尚，但拥有物理按钮可以更轻松地调节音量和使麦克风静音。我确实希望 Dot 有一种方法可以物理暂停音乐；在 Nest Mini 上，如果您点击设备的中间，音乐就会停止。</p><p>总的来说，Dot 对于大多数人来说是最好的预算选择，但我会毫不犹豫地推荐 Nest Mini 作为另一个经济实惠的智能扬声器选择。与 Alexa 相比，我通常更喜欢使用 Google Assistant，任​​何有同感的人都应该购买 Nest Mini。 Dot 的听起来确实明显更好，所以如果您打算定期听音频，那么这可能是正确的选择。但是，如果您只打算在早上准备时使用它来播放一首快歌或播客，只需选择您最喜欢的助手并从那里开始即可。</p><h2> 100 美元以下最佳智能音箱：Amazon Echo </h2><p><core-commerce id="4071c4bc3ab14a62b2e309bc135efb14" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>亚马逊、苹果和谷歌都有 100 美元的智能音箱：分别是第四代<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDg1SEs0S0w2P3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWQ2LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIyMmUzZjBiNy1jMTc5LTM5MmEtODIxYy1lNmRmNTNjMjgwYTYifQ&amp;signature=AQAAATdcQZxdYwTZKlKR3f8wqWL47-eHL5SKRgMmwrEYltFC&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB085HK4KL6%3F">Echo</a> 、 <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Walmart;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=3719d8d4-5edd-4817-998a-91f3229e7323&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Walmart&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIzNzE5ZDhkNC01ZWRkLTQ4MTctOTk4YS05MWYzMjI5ZTczMjMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud2FsbWFydC5jb20vaXAvSG9tZVBvZC1taW5pLVNwYWNlLUdyYXkvODEwNzQ2OTYxIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIyMmUzZjBiNy1jMTc5LTM5MmEtODIxYy1lNmRmNTNjMjgwYTYifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAXA5tlqyG6X6C9ACOSTnyb27FaC-pkRyIPk1k08C52Vf&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2FHomePod-mini-Space-Gray%2F810746961">HomePod mini</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Walmart;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=3719d8d4-5edd-4817-998a-91f3229e7323&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Walmart&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfTf66g1NcLyueHahQ7Wo_B-ftmspS_GfKNyJWMUNylN&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2FGoogle-Nest-Audio-Smart-Speaker-with-Google-Assistant-Chalk%2F778990339">Nest Audio</a> 。这三个公司都声称具有卓越的音频质量，因此对于很多人来说，这些扬声器将是 Echo Dot 和 Nest Mini 等小型扬声器与 Sonos Era 100 等更大、更昂贵的型号之间的最佳选择。</p><p>亚马逊再次超越了自己的实力。与 Dot 一样，最新的 Echo 也经过了彻底重新设计，新的内部结构也是以音乐为中心而设计的。它结合了一个 3 英寸低音扬声器和两个 0.8 英寸高音扬声器——比 Nest Audio 或 HomePod mini 更先进的设置。 （Google Nest Audio 使用一个 3 英寸低音扬声器，但只有一个 0.75 英寸高音扬声器，而 Apple HomePod mini 则使用一个“全频”驱动器和两个无源散热器。）</p><p>实际上，这意味着 Echo 明显比 Nest Audio 或 HomePod mini 响亮，并且比竞争对手更适合播放充满房间的声音。它还提供令人印象深刻的低音重击和强大的中频。事实上，我对扬声器的主要抱怨是高音不够清脆。将 Echo 与 Era 100 进行比较，100 听起来更加活泼，而 Echo 则显得有点浑浊。不过，100 的价格是 Echo 的两倍多。</p><p>虽然 Echo 扬声器可能在音量和低音方面击败 Nest Audio 和 HomePod mini，但谷歌和苹果的扬声器也是不错的选择。 HomePod mini 是三款扬声器中最安静的，但它在整个音频频谱中听起来仍然很平衡。低音不是太自信，但鉴于其微小的尺寸（它是迄今为止这三个扬声器中最小的），其存在感比我预期的要强。</p><p>如果您使用的是 iPhone 11 或更新机型，它还有一些不错的好处。得益于最近 iPhone 中的 U1“超宽带”芯片，HomePod mini 可以判断附近是否有手机，这使得将音乐从手机传递到扬声器（反之亦然）变得非常简单。 HomePod mini 的播放控件也会自动弹出，如果扬声器当前未播放，手机的锁定屏幕将显示音乐建议。设置也非常简单——只需将 iPhone 或 iPad 靠近扬声器，它就会自动启动该过程。</p><p>谷歌的 Nest Audio 听起来也相当好听。它的声音比 HomePod mini 稍大一些，并且低音更强。它的整体功率和表现力不如 Echo，但 100 美元的价格，它是一款平衡性良好的扬声器，应该可以满足大多数人的需求。</p><p>如果您想要更大的音量或渴望更身临其境的体验，所有这三个扬声器都支持立体声配对。只需 200 美元，两台 Echo 就能让整个大房间充满高品质的声音和足够的低音，足以为派对提供动力。一对 HomePod mini 或 Nest Audio 扬声器的功能不是那么强大，但如果您是一个更热心的听众，那么它可以带来很大的升级。工作日期间，一对 Nest Audio 或 HomePod 迷你扬声器放在我的办公桌上听起来很棒。我不需要压倒性的音量，但可以欣赏立体声分离度。其中两个扬声器一起可以轻松为更大的生活空间提供动力，尽管如果优先考虑音量，Echo 是更好的选择。</p><p>在这里，我也认为选择最适合您家中以及与其他小工具配合使用的智能助手可能是最重要的因素 - 但考虑到 Alexa 的无处不在和新 Echo 的卓越音质，它是这个价位上最好的智能扬声器。</p><h2>最佳中端智能音箱：Sonos Era 100 </h2><p><core-commerce id="25a95ee9632047bdbbbbb900dbf8b94a" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>如果你对音乐只是一时的兴趣，那么 Echo Dot 和 Nest Mini 并不能真正满足你的需求。花更多的钱升级到在设计时考虑到音频质量的扬声器是我做出的最佳决定之一。多年来，我一直没有合适的家庭音乐解决方案，但最终，适度的投资让我的生活变得更加愉快。</p><p>多年来，Sonos One 一直是我的最爱，它结合了合理的价格、良好的音质和大量有用的功能，如简单的多房间音频、立体声配对以及与大量服务的兼容性。今年，Sonos 用<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sonos;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=1e71dc69-0ad7-47e7-abf5-dc3926557fa3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sonos&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIxZTcxZGM2OS0wYWQ3LTQ3ZTctYWJmNS1kYzM5MjY1NTdmYTMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc29ub3MuY29tL2VuLXVzL3Nob3AvZXJhLTEwMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjJlM2YwYjctYzE3OS0zOTJhLTgyMWMtZTZkZjUzYzI4MGE2In0&amp;signature=AQAAAZ2QTRvlnA5n8O6YgARV32cka-FgDMGabeYoGRrBpYQW&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sonos.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Fera-100">Era 100</a>取代了 One，这是一款售价 250 美元的扬声器，几乎在您能想到的所有方面都有所改进。最重要的是，它使用了一种新的扬声器阵列，其中包括两个高音扬声器（而不是只有一个）以及一个大 25% 的低音扬声器。最终的结果是，Era 100 在音质方面轻而易举地超越了 One，具有令人印象深刻的低音、令人惊讶的巨大音量以及由于额外的高音扬声器而提高的高端清晰度。</p><p>除了音质之外，还有很多其他改进。 Era 100 使用内置麦克风更轻松地进行 Trueplay 调音，从而根据您放置的位置优化扬声器的输出。以前，您必须使用 iPhone 在房间里走动并挥舞手机才能优化您的 Sonos 扬声器，但现在这个过程要简单得多。 Era 100 还包括通过 USB-C 端口的线路输入，并且当您只想快速将设备连接到扬声器时还具有蓝牙功能。 It&#39;s a bummer that you need to buy an adapter to hook up a turntable or other audio equipment to the Era 100, but since the One didn&#39;t support line-in at all, I&#39;m still glad it&#39;s an option.</p><p> There are a handful of other small but solid improvements, like redesigned controls on the top that make it easier to skip tracks and a mic mute switch that cuts the power to the mic for extra security. Like the One, it&#39;s easy to set up Alexa or the Sonos voice assistant here, but the Era 100 <em>doesn&#39;t</em> support the Google Assistant – so if you were previously using a Sonos speaker and relied on Google, you&#39;re unfortunately out of luck here. Other than that one change, though, the Era 100 is an excellent all-around performer. It&#39;s a great speaker on its own and is also a great starting point if you want to build a multi-room audio setup.</p><p> The Amazon Echo Studio remains an excellent-sounding speaker as well, and at $199 it&#39;s a good bit cheaper than the Era 100 as well. If you want to save some cash or already have a bunch of other Echo devices in your smart home ecosystem, it makes sense as a speaker for higher-quality music playback. But given that it&#39;ll be four years old this fall, I think it makes sense to opt for a newer device that&#39;ll get longer support and updates.</p><h2> Best smart speaker for music lovers: Sonos Five </h2><p><core-commerce id="a60083cdb64d44758943efa1a26eb1e4" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> As nice as the Era 100 and Echo Studio are, there&#39;s only so much you can get out of them. If you crave more bass, clarity and stereo separation, the $550 <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sonos;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=1e71dc69-0ad7-47e7-abf5-dc3926557fa3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sonos&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIxZTcxZGM2OS0wYWQ3LTQ3ZTctYWJmNS1kYzM5MjY1NTdmYTMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc29ub3MuY29tL2VuLXVzL3Nob3AvZml2ZSIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjJlM2YwYjctYzE3OS0zOTJhLTgyMWMtZTZkZjUzYzI4MGE2In0&amp;signature=AQAAAR25cLMb2vxNkMKEVe6NeoOcX395yZzkj30eSdpml_uG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sonos.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Ffive">Sonos Five</a> is the best sounding smart speaker on this list. It has many of the conveniences in the Era 100 and sounds significantly better than any other Sonos speaker. It also sounds much better than the Echo Studio and anything Google is currently selling.</p><p> That said, the Five stretches our definition of a smart speaker here because it doesn&#39;t have a built-in voice assistant. But it&#39;s so good at music playback that it&#39;s worth recommending you pick one up along with an Echo Dot or Nest Mini. Both of those speakers work with Sonos, so you can use voice commands to control the Five just as you would a dedicated Alexa or Google Assistant device. Sonos also refreshed the speaker two years ago with a new wireless radio as well as more memory and a faster processor. This means it should stay current and work with future Sonos software updates for years to come.</p><p> Since we&#39;re talking &quot;best&quot; here, I&#39;m going to go ahead and recommend that true music junkies splash out on two Five speakers and pair them in stereo. Put simply, it&#39;s the most enjoyable experience I&#39;ve had listening to music in years; I found myself picking up new details while listening to albums I&#39;ve heard over and over again. It&#39;s a wonderful experience and worth saving for if you&#39;re a music lover. I didn&#39;t know what I was missing until I tried the Five.</p><p> The Sonos <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sonos;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=1e71dc69-0ad7-47e7-abf5-dc3926557fa3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sonos&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIxZTcxZGM2OS0wYWQ3LTQ3ZTctYWJmNS1kYzM5MjY1NTdmYTMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc29ub3MuY29tL2VuLXVzL3Nob3AvZXJhLTMwMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjJlM2YwYjctYzE3OS0zOTJhLTgyMWMtZTZkZjUzYzI4MGE2In0&amp;signature=AQAAAVjDDSsafMZzXOPRzL6yDO_3xbdyYsxSHlScfT0ot5w0&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sonos.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Fera-300">Era 300</a> , also recently released, is a $450 speaker that supports Dolby Atmos spatial audio from Apple Music and Amazon Music Unlimited. I&#39;ve found that the quality of spatial audio mixes can be very hit or miss, but the good news is that the Era 300 sounds outstanding whether it&#39;s playing back Atmos content or just standard tracks. It&#39;s not quite as good as the Sonos Five, but it does have built-in microphones for voice assistants and easy Trueplay tuning as well as Bluetooth and the redesigned controls on the Era 100. Again, the main downside is that Google Assistant isn&#39;t supported here.</p><p> Finally, if you&#39;re an Apple Music user or have a lot of Apple hardware in your home, the second-generation <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Apple;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=4130e2f0-a14f-4c5e-bdab-cd52ac7d8e79&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Apple&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI0MTMwZTJmMC1hMTRmLTRjNWUtYmRhYi1jZDUyYWM3ZDhlNzkiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYXBwbGUuY29tL2hvbWVwb2QvIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIyMmUzZjBiNy1jMTc5LTM5MmEtODIxYy1lNmRmNTNjMjgwYTYifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAZLnR3S2KbD5Q6PLJUnEcdOnwGDQLbiRbs0LzN41wTFq&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apple.com%2Fhomepod%2F">HomePod</a> is definitely worth considering. At $300, it&#39;s a lot cheaper than these Sonos speakers but supports spatial audio like the Era 300. The Era 300 and Sonos Five are better speakers overall (and certainly much louder), but there&#39;s a lot to like about the HomePod&#39;s audio quality at its price point. It&#39;s a clear, crisp vocal-forward speaker, and its design and software processing does a great job of making music sound like it&#39;s all around you, even if you&#39;re not playing back Dolby Atmos tracks.</p><h2> Best portable smart speaker: Sonos Roam </h2><p><core-commerce id="ad8441cad45a4faabcbc0e9b04740ef1" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> While many people will be happy with a few speakers strategically placed throughout their home, you might want something that works outside as well as inside. Fortunately, you can find speakers that pair voice controls and strong music playback performance with portable, weatherproof form factors. For my money, it&#39;s hard to beat the <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sonos;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=1e71dc69-0ad7-47e7-abf5-dc3926557fa3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sonos&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIxZTcxZGM2OS0wYWQ3LTQ3ZTctYWJmNS1kYzM5MjY1NTdmYTMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc29ub3MuY29tL2VuLXVzL3Nob3Avcm9hbSIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjJlM2YwYjctYzE3OS0zOTJhLTgyMWMtZTZkZjUzYzI4MGE2In0&amp;signature=AQAAAeq2_H9R60wVGN9EP4TrWro8mlqbdOt9_4uJX6UE_CCp&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sonos.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Froam">Sonos Roam</a> for sheer versatility, not to mention audio quality.</p><p> When used inside the home, the Roam works like any other Sonos speaker. It fits in with an existing multi-room Sonos setup, or you can get a pair for stereo playback. Like most other Sonos speakers, it works with the Sonos Voice Assistant, Google Assistant or Amazon Alexa, and it supports essentially every major music service available. It sounds very good given its tiny size; it&#39;s quieter and not quite as clear as the Sonos One or the Era 100, but it still packs a surprising bass thump and distinct highs.</p><p> Since it was designed with on-the-go usage in mind, the Roam has a battery and Bluetooth so you can take it anywhere and use it far away from your WiFi network. And its diminutive size makes it easy to take it everywhere, both around the house and out and about. It&#39;s also the first Sonos speaker that is fully waterproof, as well as dust- and drop-resistant, so you shouldn&#39;t worry about taking it to the pool or beach.</p><p> The Roam gets about 10 hours of battery life, whether you&#39;re on WiFI or Bluetooth. There are other portable speakers that last longer, so if you&#39;re really going to push the battery you might be better served by another option.</p><p> Another wireless portable speaker option is the $449 <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sonos;elmt:;cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=1e71dc69-0ad7-47e7-abf5-dc3926557fa3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sonos&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5zb25vcy5jb20vZW4tdXMvc2hvcC9tb3ZlLTIiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjIyZTNmMGI3LWMxNzktMzkyYS04MjFjLWU2ZGY1M2MyODBhNiJ9&amp;signature=AQAAASZXj7NCTsNbpVKA0c7B-T3ECu1TAYuWww9ProYCD-IL&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sonos.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Fmove-2" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.sonos.com/en-us/shop/move-2">Sonos Move 2</a> . It&#39;s much larger and louder than the Roam, which is unsurprising given how much more expensive it is. It&#39;s a nice upgrade over the previous Move, with two tweeters for more detailed sound, a battery that lasts more than a day and redesigned touch controls up top. It also has a line-in jack via USB-C, so you can hook up a turntable when you&#39;re using it inside. If you&#39;re willing to sacrifice portability for power and better sound quality (and can afford it), the Move 2 will be more satisfying than the Roam.</p><p> A better choice than the Move, unless you already have other Sonos products, is the $399 <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcJ8lMPA4i0iXXFpC6cy2D1NxIuyoKaZL6BUuU7fBz7v&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBose-Portable-Home-Speaker-Built%2Fdp%2FB07VFKBQ3K%3Fth%3D1">Bose Portable Smart speaker</a> . It supports Alexa and Google Assistant commands, and since it can connect to WiFi, you can ask your preferred assistant to play music from Spotify, Amazon Music and other services. On top of that, it produces well-rounded sound, sports an IPX4 design with a convenient carry handle and will last up to 12 hours on a single charge.</p><p> Bose also has a good alternative to the Roam. The $149 <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWApfm9Tkcg4KZ_ozvq88khu_GJ_3edD8nKreQxBN7lX&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBose-SoundLink-Bluetooth-Portable-Waterproof%2Fdp%2FB099TJGJ91%3Fth%3D1">SoundLink Flex</a> supports Siri and Google Assistant commands, plus it has an IP67 design that&#39;s roughly the size of a small clutch bag. It pumps out bright, dynamic sound and can pair with other speakers for stereo sound, too – it&#39;s excellent and slightly cheaper than the Roam.</p><p> While this guide is all about smart speakers, we&#39;d be remiss if we didn&#39;t mention all of the solid portable speakers out there that either have limited smart features or none at all. We have <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-portable-bluetooth-speakers-133004551.html">an entire guide</a> to the best portable Bluetooth speakers, so if you&#39;re purely concerned with portability and less about having an ecosystem of connected speakers, there are lots of options worth investigating.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-smart-speakers-151515264.html?src=rss]]>;</description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-smart-speakers-151515264.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 22e3f0b7-c179-392a-821c-e6df53c280a6</guid><dc:creator> Nathan Ingraham</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 20 Sep 2023 13:00:06 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1695214807</ingested><modified> 2023-09-20T13:00:18+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[amazon]]></category><category><![CDATA[BuyersGuide]]></category><category><![CDATA[smarthome2020]]></category><category><![CDATA[thebuyersguide]]></category><category><![CDATA[google]]></category><category><![CDATA[sonos]]></category><category><![CDATA[gear]]></category><category><![CDATA[home]]></category><category><![CDATA[ElectronicEquipment,Instruments&Components]]></category><category><![CDATA[Home&Garden]]></category><category><![CDATA[ElectronicsAccessories]]></category><category><![CDATA[Lifestyle(houseAndHome)]]></category><category><![CDATA[DIY&HomeImprovement]]></category><category><![CDATA[OfficeElectronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology&Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Speakers & Headphones]]></category><category><![CDATA[Audio Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Nathan Ingraham]]></category><media:content height="1600" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/a12ab710-cc29-11ed-abef-f71b78c368d5" width="2400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1600" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/a12ab710-cc29-11ed-abef-f71b78c368d5" width="2400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Nathan Ingraham / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[The latest Sonos speaker, the Era 100]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Sonos Era 100 smart speaker]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best smartphones for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Choosing the best smartphone for your needs can be challenging. With so many brands offering similar features at similar prices, it can be hard to understand what device actually has the things you want. If you&#39;ve already determined you only want <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-iphone-13-and-13-mini-review-130035113.html">an iPhone</a> , your decision-making process is slightly easier. (And even then, <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Apple;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=4130e2f0-a14f-4c5e-bdab-cd52ac7d8e79&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Apple&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI0MTMwZTJmMC1hMTRmLTRjNWUtYmRhYi1jZDUyYWM3ZDhlNzkiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYXBwbGUuY29tL2lwaG9uZS8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImZjYTY5ODU2LTYwNzEtNDdiZC1hYmFkLTg5MTZmYThiNDMyNyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAX-68mMsUTLsMwRHcmvlHuu4RBCrg99159ozxPJyymuJ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apple.com%2Fiphone%2F">Apple&#39;s lineup</a> offers more options than ever.) Those also considering Android will have even more options to choose from, and likely more questions. Do you want a <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-02-11-samsung-galaxy-s20-cameras-ai-tools-space-zooms.html">camera that can zoom into subjects that are extremely far away</a> , or do you want intuitive AI that can screen your incoming calls for you? Here at Engadget, we test smartphones all year round and can help you make sense of what&#39;s available and what to look out for. And, of course, we&#39;ve included our top picks to help you whittle down your shortlist.</p><h2>安卓还是iOS？</h2><p> When you&#39;re searching for the best smartphone, it becomes clear that each OS has its pros and cons. Apple&#39;s tight-knit ecosystem makes it super easy to share data between iPhones, iPads and Macs or seamlessly hand-off phone calls or music from one device to another. At the same time, you&#39;re effectively locked in, as services like Apple Messages aren&#39;t available on other platforms.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> As for Android, there&#39;s a much wider range of handsets from companies like Google, Samsung, Sony and more. However, Android phones don&#39;t enjoy that same length of software support and often have lower trade-in values. In short, there&#39;s no wrong answer. However, you will want to consider how your phone will fit in with the rest of your devices. So unless you&#39;re really fed up with one OS and willing to learn another, it probably doesn&#39;t make a lot of sense to switch from an iPhone to an Android phone (or vice versa) – especially if everyone else in your household is using the same platform.</p><h2> Cameras</h2><p> Since your cell phone often pulls double duty as your primary camera, figuring out what kind of photo tools you want is key. Nowadays, practically every mobile phone can take a great picture in bright light. But if you want a long optical zoom, you&#39;ll probably have to upgrade to a more expensive device. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-10/91a42bf0-305d-11ec-9f9f-636d29742095" alt="Close up of the Pixel 6 Pro's camera bump." data-uuid="9d43d937-5132-30a6-9eb2-c8bb1c893521"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Cherlynn Low / Engadget</div></figure><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-engadget-guide-to-the-best-midrange-smartphones-120050366.html">Mid-range phones</a> often only have two rear cameras (a primary wide-angle lens and a secondary ultra-wide camera) and can sometimes struggle in low-light situations. Each phone maker also has various features that might be a better fit for your style, with Apple offering four different color presets on the latest iPhones, while Google&#39;s Pixel 7 comes with neat tools like dedicated long exposure and action pan modes.</p><h2> Will you get 5G or Wi-Fi 6?</h2><p> The good news is that in 2022, most phones have at least 802.11ac Wi-Fi and support for one or more types of 5G connectivity. However, if you want the fastest wireless speeds you can get, it&#39;s going to cost you a bit more. For example, on certain networks, mmWave 5G offers up to gigabit download speeds, less latency and better bandwidth. But mmWave 5G also requires more sophisticated (and pricier) modems, which means support for it is often missing from budget and mid-range handsets like the iPhone SE.</p><p> On the bright side, mmWave 5G isn&#39;t as widely available as other versions of 5G, so depending on where you live and what network you&#39;re on, you may not be missing out on much if you buy a phone that doesn&#39;t support it. It&#39;s a similar situation for Wi-Fi 6 and Wi-Fi 6e, which are available on a number of high-end devices, but harder to find on less expensive handsets. Wi-Fi 6 also requires you have to have a compatible router, so unless you know you need it or have a specific use case in mind, the lack of support for mmWave 5G or Wi-Fi 6E shouldn&#39;t be a dealbreaker when looking for a new phone.</p><h2> Other features to consider</h2><p> Because not everyone agrees on what makes the best phone, you should think about any other specs that might be extra important for you. Mobile gamers will almost certainly appreciate the 120Hz refresh rates you get on phones like the Samsung Galaxy S23 or the Apple iPhone 15 Pro. Alternatively, if long battery life is important, you&#39;ll probably want to go with a larger iPhone or an Android phone with a battery that&#39;s between 4,000 and 5,000 mAh in size. Meanwhile, if you find yourself juggling a lot of devices, it can be really nice to have a phone that supports reverse wireless charging, which on Samsung phones even lets you recharge the company&#39;s Galaxy Watches.</p><h2> Best iOS smartphone: iPhone 15 Pro </h2><p><core-commerce id="1da6e07c962e4140824f8e003c8aec30" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> The changes to the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Walmart;elmt:;cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=3719d8d4-5edd-4817-998a-91f3229e7323&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Walmart&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy53YWxtYXJ0LmNvbS9pcC9BVC1ULWlQaG9uZS0xNS1Qcm8tMTI4R0ItTmF0dXJhbC1UaXRhbml1bS81MDU0NjA1Mzg0IiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJmY2E2OTg1Ni02MDcxLTQ3YmQtYWJhZC04OTE2ZmE4YjQzMjcifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAbb6nSIkJ0tvocj6sobLjMh91IjnS7n-z-c0aQ9xAtv4&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2FAT-T-iPhone-15-Pro-128GB-Natural-Titanium%2F5054605384" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.walmart.com/ip/AT-T-iPhone-15-Pro-128GB-Natural-Titanium/5054605384">iPhone 15 Pro and Pro Max</a> may seem small when considered on their own, but together they add up to more than the sum of their parts. For the iPhone 15 Pro Max, in particular, the smaller, lighter titanium build means it might be within the realm of consideration for many shoppers for the first time. It&#39;s no longer sharp and hefty like a weapon, but still has one of the longest-lasting batteries on the market.</p><p> The larger handset also gets a new 5x telephoto camera that helps it catch up to flagships on the Android side, which have had zoom lenses for years. Though Apple doesn&#39;t outclass the competition on photography, it&#39;s certainly closed the gap and you&#39;ll find great cameras on both the Pro and Pro Max. They also have updated portrait effects and editing tools, so photography is improved whether you&#39;re shooting faraway subjects or something just in front of you.</p><p> Both <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/iphone-15-pro-max-review-apple-makes-a-strong-case-for-its-biggest-phone-130018980.html">iPhone 15 Pro</a> models have the new Action Button and USB-C charging, the latter of which will be more meaningful in a couple of years when the world presumably ditches Lightning at last. The Action Button, meanwhile, takes the often unused mute slider and gives you the option of mapping a frequently used shortcut to it, so you can quickly launch the camera, flashlight, voice recorder or magnifier. Having this many ways to configure the Action Button means it&#39;s far more useful to more people than a simple toggle for silencing your phone.</p><p> This year&#39;s A17 Pro chip not only brings excellent performance, but its six-core GPU also enables console-level gaming and hardware-accelerated ray tracing for realistic lighting effects. Later this year, you can dig into titles like <em>Resident Evil Village</em> and, in early 2024, <em>Assassin&#39;s Creed</em> <em>Mirage</em> on the iPhone 15 Pro and Pro Max. You&#39;ll also get a second-generation ultra wideband chip for improved precision object location, and reverse USB charging so you can power up your accessories in a pinch.</p><p> When you consider all these features as a whole, the iPhone 15 Pro and Pro Max are not just a solid upgrade from their predecessors, they&#39;re also among the best phones around. <em>– Cherlynn Low, Deputy Editor</em></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/iphone-15-pro-max-review-apple-makes-a-strong-case-for-its-biggest-phone-130018980.html"><strong>Read our full review of the iPhone 15 Pro Max</strong></a></p><h2> Best Android smartphone: Samsung Galaxy S23 Ultra </h2><p><core-commerce id="0a890277b10447538a197ef0469cf481" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> The <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Samsung Electronics;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f85e63cd-e13c-4f9d-991c-9fbaadede3ac&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Samsung+Electronics&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZGemkE8rFWMfFLtwCMzUqffJ8m6AKGTEEjf52a9rIaj&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samsung.com%2Fus%2Fsmartphones%2Fgalaxy-s23-ultra%2Fbuy%2Fgalaxy-s23-ultra-512gb-unlocked-sm-s918uzgfxaa%2F">Galaxy S23 Ultra</a> has pretty much everything you could want or need on a super premium flagship phone. It features a gorgeous 6.8-inch AMOLED display with a 120Hz refresh rate, a speedy Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 chip, longer battery life and a built-in S Pen for all your drawing and notetaking needs. New for 2023 is a huge 200MP sensor for the phone&#39;s main camera, which comes with improved OIS, 8K/30fps video recording and some additional photography tools in the Expert RAW app.</p><p> The main downsides are that starting at $1,200, the S23 Ultra is as expensive as ever, and while its advanced photo and video features have a lot of potential, you need to put in some extra time and effort to get the most out of them. And because the phone&#39;s design, display and most of its cameras are so similar to previous models, anyone who bought an S22 last year can safely skip upgrading this time around. But for people who want a true do-everything handset, the S23 Ultra is in a class of its own and is our pick for the best Android phone. <em>– Sam Rutherford, Senior Reporter</em></p><h2> Best midrange Android smartphone: Google Pixel 7a </h2><p><core-commerce id="a5f3e898e7dc48c0a575ee88a9d17422" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> The $500 <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3N0b3JlLmdvb2dsZS5jb20vP3BsaT0xJmhsPWVuLVVTIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJmY2E2OTg1Ni02MDcxLTQ3YmQtYWJhZC04OTE2ZmE4YjQzMjcifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAXa17_GAonKLxGFRZWKPj2Q11Gy5lxBn1M8V5wP9Vc8J&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fstore.google.com%2F%3Fpli%3D1%26hl%3Den-US">Pixel 7a</a> delivers everything we look for in a great affordable phone. New features include a faster Tensor G2 chip, a smoother 90Hz display and for the first time on one of Google&#39;s A-series phones: support for wireless charging. And with a refreshed design with IP67 water resistance, it looks and feels like the standard Pixel 7 but for $100 less. You also get great support thanks to five years of security updates and at least three OS upgrades. The phone&#39;s only shortcomings are rather small and include a lack of a dedicated zoom lens and no support for mmWave 5G (unless you purchase a slightly more expensive $550 model from Verizon). <em>– SR</em></p><h2> Best midrange iPhone: iPhone SE (2022) </h2><p><core-commerce id="902d2130357540648b07cbc78df45638" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> With an A15 Bionic chip and iOS 15, the latest Apple <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Apple;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=4130e2f0-a14f-4c5e-bdab-cd52ac7d8e79&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Apple&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI0MTMwZTJmMC1hMTRmLTRjNWUtYmRhYi1jZDUyYWM3ZDhlNzkiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYXBwbGUuY29tL2lwaG9uZS1zZS8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImZjYTY5ODU2LTYwNzEtNDdiZC1hYmFkLTg5MTZmYThiNDMyNyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAcaqyVrhQuOjjXvhwaJ2rVs78n6Lwg3mPQtkIpOqdriI&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apple.com%2Fiphone-se%2F">iPhone SE</a> is possibly the most powerful phone you can find for under $450. Sure, it has a dated design, but some folks might actually appreciate the retro look. The best thing about the iPhone SE is its home button: It&#39;s the only new iPhone to have Touch ID. And though it only has a single rear camera, the SE still takes solid pictures. If you can get over the small, low-res screen, the iPhone SE will serve you well. It&#39;s also really the only sub-$500 option for iOS diehards.</p><p> If you&#39;re open to considering Android and want to spend less than $400, consider something from Samsung&#39;s Galaxy A-series or the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:OnePlus;elmt:;cpos:11;pos:1;pdid:OnePlus Nord N20" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=d8d4d385-7f93-4537-83d1-d5fb47d219ec&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=OnePlus&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5vbmVwbHVzLmNvbS9uMjAtNWciLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImZjYTY5ODU2LTYwNzEtNDdiZC1hYmFkLTg5MTZmYThiNDMyNyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAQzRbF2KHrJR4NURLCBHep8rOkdE1vLtUY9aSqbSj9Ly&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oneplus.com%2Fn20-5g" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://go.skimresources.com/?id=72705X1521812&amp;xs=1&amp;xcreo=500002&amp;url=https://www.oneplus.com/n20-5g">OnePlus Nord N20</a> . Those looking to spend even less can check out the <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9Nb3RvLUJhdHRlcnktVW5sb2NrZWQtTW90b3JvbGEtQ2FtZXJhL2RwL0IwOVNNNkdSNEI_bGlua0NvZGU9c2wxJmxpbmtJZD01YWRkZjI5M2RlNzM5ZTUxMzk0ZDQ0YWE5NjYwOGEzNCZsYW5ndWFnZT1lbl9VUyZyZWZfPWFzX2xpX3NzX3RsJnRhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTd6LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJmY2E2OTg1Ni02MDcxLTQ3YmQtYWJhZC04OTE2ZmE4YjQzMjcifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAVEgGmQKhpXt1qlD4MLbf0_Doetx4d8-JXT0Pi4l_Mlr&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FMoto-Battery-Unlocked-Motorola-Camera%2Fdp%2FB09SM6GR4B%3FlinkCode%3Dsl1%26linkId%3D5addf293de739e51394d44aa96608a34%26language%3Den_US%26ref_%3Das_li_ss_tl">Moto G Power</a> – just be prepared to compromise on features like display and cameras at these lower price points. <em>– CL</em></p><h2> Best camera on a smartphone: Pixel 7 Pro </h2><p><core-commerce id="501687161a8c47cfa134427cbf956f6a" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> It&#39;s hard for me to leave the house without the <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcRBeZqSNwZi3X7rz4uHrXDl3Z4HeogWPbzHEmlZEW_4&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGoogle-Pixel-Pro-Smartphone-Telephoto%2Fdp%2FB0BCQVFQHD%2F">Pixel 7 Pro</a> , my pick for best camera phone. As long as there&#39;s a chance I might want to take photos, I make sure I&#39;ve brought Google&#39;s latest flagship. The Pixel 7 Pro&#39;s triple rear camera system is versatile enough to capture anything from the largest group shots or wide landscapes to faraway animals (like that time I thought I spotted a whale when staring at a distant blob from Acadia National Park). Google&#39;s Night Sight still outperforms the competition when taking pictures in low lighting conditions, too, and its computational photography delivers clear, vivid photos.</p><p> Of course, Samsung and Apple&#39;s flagships are closing the gap, and these days there is little difference between the photos they deliver. Some people might even prefer the warmer tint on Galaxy devices. But special features like Google&#39;s Magic Eraser and Motion effects make the Pixel 7 Pro the most fun to shoot with. Plus, I love the additional tools you get on Pixel phones, like Call Screening, Material You theming and Live Captions, among others. <em>– CL</em></p><h2> Best foldable for multitasking: Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5 </h2><p><core-commerce id="" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p><core-commerce id="58e649ab39904b91b248422d55d2e5fc" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> While Samsung didn&#39;t make a ton of changes to the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL1NBTVNVTkctU3RvcmFnZS1VbmxvY2tlZC1TbWFydHBob25lLVN0cmVhbWluZy9kcC9CMEM2M1FHR0JLP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTd6LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJmY2E2OTg1Ni02MDcxLTQ3YmQtYWJhZC04OTE2ZmE4YjQzMjcifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAf3EwFJfqLwU8tJ-cBjYXxNWb2sdUMspJ30DAeZ2lHnD&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSAMSUNG-Storage-Unlocked-Smartphone-Streaming%2Fdp%2FB0C63QGGBK" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/SAMSUNG-Storage-Unlocked-Smartphone-Streaming/dp/B0C63QGGBK">Z Fold 5</a> , it&#39;s still the best big flexible phone on the market. As before, you get native stylus support, IPX8 water resistance (good for dunks of up to five feet for 30 minutes) and of course, a stunning 7.6-inch main display. New for 2023 is a faster Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 chip, improved brightness, expanded multitasking capabilities and most importantly, a completely redesigned hinge. Not only does Samsung&#39;s new Flex hinge eliminate the gap between the two sides of the phone when it&#39;s closed (to help keep dust out), it also makes the phone thinner (down to 13.4mm from 15.8mm), which is a nice change for what was already a somewhat bulky device. The biggest issue remains its price: Samsung&#39;s latest flagship foldable remains exorbitantly expensive at $1,800. <em>— SR</em></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/galaxy-z-fold-5-review-five-years-in-samsung-is-treading-water-140002461.html"><strong>Read our full review of the Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5</strong></a></p><h2> Best foldable for selfies: Samsung Galaxy Z Flip 5 </h2><p><core-commerce id="403db61227b64666aa9dfda4e28eccee" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If you&#39;re shopping for a foldable in the US, you actually have choices now. The clear winner of that race in the flip-phone category, though, continues to be Samsung. While Motorola&#39;s Razr+ gave the Galaxy Z Flip series some serious competition, it still wasn&#39;t good enough. With this year&#39;s <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQzYzS0Q3SlA_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tN3otMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImZjYTY5ODU2LTYwNzEtNDdiZC1hYmFkLTg5MTZmYThiNDMyNyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAUXnD5tUeUHog9qpQRXy6jmFBDM0MhH9rQQTa0EztMFt&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0C63KD7JP" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0C63KD7JP">Z Flip 5</a> , Samsung brought a larger external display that&#39;s more functional than previous generations. You&#39;ll have to jump through a few hoops to enable full-sized apps and maximize the experience on that screen, but once you do, the Flip 5 realizes its potential.</p><p> This year, Samsung also updated the hinges on its Z series, using a new dual-rail structure that&#39;s supposed to better diffuse impact than before. It also creates a water drop-shaped crease that the company says results in less stress on the screen, which should improve overall durability. Even if your Flip does break, Samsung is better positioned to handle repairs than any other foldable maker in the US, since it&#39;s the most established player here.</p><p> The Flip 5 also has superior cameras compared to the Moto Razr+, delivering richer, more saturated colors in daylight. Of course, don&#39;t expect flagship-level pictures from any flip-style foldable. The Flip 5 pales in comparison to the likes of the latest iPhone or Pixel in low light, but for the most part, its pictures will be good enough for Instagram. Plus, you&#39;ll have a lot more fun snapping selfies or group photos with a foldable, since it can act as its own tripod when flexed and you can see yourself in the external display. And don&#39;t forget Samsung&#39;s handy open-palm gesture that triggers a camera timer, which will make capturing stills or videos much easier from a distance.</p><p> When it&#39;s time to kick back on your couch, the Flip 5 also delivers. It has the fastest processor on a foldable and a vibrant internal screen that refreshes at up to 120Hz for smooth scrolling and animations. It doesn&#39;t have the longest battery life, especially when compared to non-folding flagships like the Galaxy S23. But if you don&#39;t mind charging your phone whenever you&#39;re near an outlet, and a flipping foldable is on your shopping list, the Galaxy Z Flip 5 is the best foldable with this form factor. <em>— CL</em></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-z-flip-5-review-still-the-best-flip-foldable-163030055.html"><strong>Read our full review of the Samsung Galaxy Z Flip 5</strong></a></p><h2>常见问题解答</h2><h3>How do I know which smartphone is the best for me?</h3><p> While choosing the best smartphone can be challenging, it mostly comes down to how you plan on using the device. All of the best smartphones available now get the basics right — you&#39;ll be able to make calls, text and access the internet without many hiccups. If your smartphone is your most used gadget, you may want to consider paying for a device on the higher end of the price spectrum. That will get you better overall performance, higher-quality cameras and a phone that will last for many years. If you don&#39;t use your phone for everything, you may be able to compromise on performance and extra perks and spend less on a still-capable handset.</p><h3> How much is a smartphone?</h3><p> Smartphones range in price from $300 to over $1,500. The best budget phones available now will usually compromise on overall performance, design, camera prowess and extra features to keep costs down. On the flip side, the most expensive phones will have powerful processors, triple-camera arrays and even flip or fold designs. Most people will find a smartphone that fits their needs somewhere in the middle of that wide price range — we&#39;ve found that most of the best smartphones available right now cost between $500 and $1,000.</p><h3> What can you do on a smartphone?</h3><p> Smartphones are essentially small, portable computers that let you do things like check email, browse social media, follow map directions, make contactless payments and more. This is all on top of the basics like making phone calls and texting, which we&#39;ve come to expect in all modern cell phones. Smartphones have also mostly replaced compact cameras thanks to their high-quality, built-in shooters, and the fact that most smartphones today as just as portable, if not more so, as compact cameras.</p><h3> How long do smartphones last?</h3><p> Smartphones can last years and people are <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://www.computerweekly.com/news/252524995/Smartphone-trade-value-rises-as-average-age-of-devices-breaks-35-year-threshold">holding on to their phones</a> longer now than ever before. Software updates and battery life are two of the biggest factors that can affect smartphone longevity. Apple promises five years worth of software updates for its latest iPhones, and Google promises the same for its Pixel phones. Samsung phones will get four years worth of Android updates from the time they launch. As for charging speeds and battery life, your phone can deteriorate over time as you use and recharge your phone on a regular basis.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-smartphones-140004900.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-smartphones-140004900.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> fca69856-6071-47bd-abad-8916fa8b4327</guid><dc:creator> Cherlynn Low,Sam Rutherford</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 20 Sep 2023 12:00:29 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1695212878</ingested><modified> 2023-09-20T12:28:12+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Telecommunication]]></category><category><![CDATA[Shopping]]></category><category><![CDATA[Smart Phones]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadge