data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/a231cb60-5795-11ee-9fcf-aace1fec65e5" style="height:380px;width:675px;" alt="TMA" data-uuid="c4d95dc6-d1f6-35e7-b8d5-f12efe584c3b"><figcaption></figcaption> <div class="photo-credit">Microsoft</div></figure></a><p> The most leftfield part, though, might be a letter from Xbox chief Phil Spencer talking about Nintendo. He said Nintendo was a prime asset for Microsoft&#39;s continued push in gaming and could be the company&#39;s best bet for consumer relevance. Spencer added Nintendo had a board of directors that had not pushed for increases in market growth in ages — indicating, of course, a massive difference in how Nintendo governs itself compared to Microsoft. Eventually, Xbox bought gaming giants, including Bethesda and Activision Blizzard, so fewer plumbers and more gunners.</p><p> Microsoft has attempted to acquire the Japanese gaming giant for a while. When <em>Bloomberg</em> published an in-depth on the development of Xbox in 2021, it revealed that Microsoft execs had asked Nintendo if it was willing to be acquired — and were laughed out of the room.</p><p> By the end of yesterday, Spencer commented on X, saying: “so much has changed” since those documents. He added the company “will share the real plans when we are ready.”</p><p> — Mat Smith</p><p>​​</p><h3> The biggest stories you might have missed</h3><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-chan-zuckerberg-initiative-is-building-a-massive-gpu-cluster-to-cure-prevent-or-manage-all-diseases-205454041.html">The Chan Zuckerberg Initiative is building a massive GPU cluster to &#39;cure, prevent or manage all diseases&#39;</a></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/we-put-the-dyson-zones-air-filters-to-the-test-heres-what-we-found-133014523.html">We put the Dyson Zone&#39;s air filters to the test. Here&#39;s what we found.</a></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-ai-researchers-mistakenly-leaked-38tb-of-company-data-094659079.html">Microsoft AI researchers mistakenly leaked 38TB of company data</a></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/netgears-new-wallet-busting-orbi-router-has-just-about-every-feature-imaginable-123035066.html">Netgear&#39;s new wallet-busting Orbi router has just about every feature imaginable</a></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/how-to-watch-and-follow-thursdays-microsoft-surface-event-150034227.html">How to watch and follow Thursday&#39;s Microsoft Surface event</a></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/talos-principle-2-and-the-quiet-subversion-of-optimistic-sci-fi-160014360.html">Talos Principle 2 and the quiet subversion of optimistic sci-fi</a></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/can-microsofts-surface-pcs-get-out-of-their-rut-175518777.html">Can Microsoft&#39;s Surface PCs get out of their rut?</a></p><p></p><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/iphone-15-pro-max-review-apple-makes-a-strong-case-for-its-biggest-phone-130018980.html">iPhone 15 Pro Max review</a></h2><h3> Apple makes the strongest case yet for its biggest, priciest phone.</h3> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/iphone-15-pro-max-review-apple-makes-a-strong-case-for-its-biggest-phone-130018980.html"><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/f6a64720-5795-11ee-9f07-0935e62c4776" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/f6a64720-5795-11ee-9f07-0935e62c4776" style="height:450px;width:675px;" alt="TMA" data-uuid="e2cf3c3d-0c0c-375a-ac13-b49fa55e3c6f"><figcaption></figcaption> <div class="photo-credit">Engadget</div></figure></a><p> It&#39;s the year of the USB-C iPhone, and the iPhone 15 Pro Max adds a new action button and the most versatile camera system yet. Apple has kept the same price for the Pro ($999) and Pro Max ($1,199) while doubling the storage capacity on the base model of the latter. If you&#39;ve been holding on to an iPhone that&#39;s at least two years old (or even just a year old), this could well be the year to upgrade. The changes coming to Apple&#39;s Pro handsets feel meatier than before, and a new titanium build makes these devices seem fresher too.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/iphone-15-pro-max-review-apple-makes-a-strong-case-for-its-biggest-phone-130018980.html"><strong>Continue reading.</strong></a></p><p></p><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/huge-leak-reveals-microsoft-will-launch-an-all-digital-xbox-series-x-and-new-gyro-controller-090442796.html">Microsoft plans an all-digital Xbox Series X and haptic controller</a></h2><h3> The console could land November 2024.</h3><h3></h3><p> Microsoft is planning a mid-generation refresh of the Xbox Series X with a new discless cylindrical design, according to those leaked documents. Microsoft previously said it has no plans for a mid-gen console refresh, but that doesn&#39;t appear to be true according to the document. In fact, the company may be working on three new consoles. The first, codenamed Ellewood, is a light refresh of the Xbox Series S (set to arrive around September 2024), while Brooklin, tentatively planned for November 2024, is a new discless version of the Xbox Series X.</p><p> Another model, XDL, matches Brooklin&#39;s specs but will presumably offer Xbox Design Lab customization. Another slide details a two-tone Sebile controller with built-in accelerometers and haptics that would make it more like Sony&#39;s latest DualSense controller. There are apparently some sustainability tweaks, like a swappable battery, recycled materials and improved repairability. If you&#39;re looking even further into the future, the documents also detailed a cloud hybrid Xbox for 2028, which would combine console power with cloud strength.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/huge-leak-reveals-microsoft-will-launch-an-all-digital-xbox-series-x-and-new-gyro-controller-090442796.html"><strong>Continue reading.</strong></a></p><p></p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/neuralink-opens-enrollment-for-its-first-human-bci-implants-215822024.html">Neuralink opens enrollment for its first human-brain-computer interfaces</a></h2><h3> The company wants to test its implants on people with quadriplegia.</h3><h3></h3><p> Elon Musk&#39;s Neuralink company, purveyors of the experimental N1 brain-computer interface (BCI), <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://neuralink.com/blog/first-clinical-trial-open-for-recruitment/">announced on Tuesday</a> it has finally opened enrollment for its first human study.</p><p> The study “aims to evaluate the safety of our implant (N1) and surgical robot (R1) and assess the initial functionality of our BCI for enabling people with paralysis to control external devices with their thoughts.” As such, this study is looking primarily for “those who have quadriplegia due to cervical spinal cord injury or amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS).” The release adds: “The initial goal of our BCI is to grant people the ability to control a computer cursor or keyboard using their thoughts alone.”</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/neuralink-opens-enrollment-for-its-first-human-bci-implants-215822024.html"><strong>Continue reading.</strong></a></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-huge-xbox-leak-reveals-an-all-digital-series-x-and-a-lot-more-111449389.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-huge-xbox-leak-reveals-an-all-digital-series-x-and-a-lot-more-111449389.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 23fa0175-5c03-40ad-8c38-fcca3bd3ed4d</guid><dc:creator> Mat Smith</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 20 Sep 2023 11:14:49 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1695201858</ingested><modified> 2023-09-20T09:24:29+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Game Consoles]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mat Smith]]></category><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/00499530-48ef-11ee-a8ce-07940362bddf" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/00499530-48ef-11ee-a8ce-07940362bddf" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Xbox]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Image of new Xbox Series S console.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Xbox Series S in Carbon Black]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Yelp has a wall of shame for businesses caught paying for fake reviews]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Since 2012, Yelp has caught nearly 5,000 businesses engaging in shady tactics, like paying customers for favorable ratings or hiring people to write phony reviews. Now, the company has a new tool to help people — and maybe the feds — track businesses that have tried to manipulate their standing on the review platform.</p><p> Yelp is releasing a new index that tracks every US establishment it&#39;s ever caught engaging in “suspicious” activity to influence its reviews. The company has made some of this information available in the past. Yelp places temporary <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://trust.yelp.com/consumer-alerts/"><ins>alerts</ins></a> on businesses&#39; pages when it discovers fake reviews, and regularly releases transparency reports detailing its moderation efforts. But the index is the first time the company has offered a single <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://trust.yelp.com/consumer-alerts/all"><ins>place</ins></a> where users can find a historical record of every business that&#39;s ever been subject to such a warning as well as a <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://trust.yelp.com/consumer-alerts/quarterly-alerts"><ins>current list</ins></a> of businesses with active alerts on their pages .</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> For Yelp, the index is both its latest move in a long-running war on fake reviews, as well as a nod to a changing regulatory environment in which fake reviews are attracting increasing scrutiny from regulators. The FTC recently proposed a <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-ftc-plans-to-slap-companies-with-hefty-fines-for-using-fake-reviews-192833691.html"><ins>formal ban</ins></a> on fake reviews with penalties of up to $50,000 for businesses caught buying, selling or manipulating online reviews.</p><p> Yelp has said it <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://blog.yelp.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Yelp-Comments-to-P214504_Jan-2023.pdf"><ins>supports</ins></a> such a rule. The company&#39;s head of user operations, Noorie Malik, points out the company has previously worked with the FTC to notify them when it discovers fake reviews and the sometimes <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/01/25/travel/fake-review-investigators.html"><ins>complex</ins></a> operations behind them. “We&#39;d love to get to a place where this new index develops into a regular resource for others, whether it&#39;s FTC, consumers, regulators or other sites,” Malik tells Engadget.</p><p> But she&#39;s also quick to point out that the index is also meant to help Yelp users make “educated decisions” about where to spend their money. While you may not think much about visiting a coffee shop with a history of paying people to leave positive Yelp reviews, your feelings may be very different if you&#39;re looking for a contractor to remodel your home, or for a daycare or moving company (all of which appear in the index).</p><p> Of course, fake reviews isn&#39;t just a Yelp problem. Malik notes that phony reviews are often coordinated on other websites among organized groups of review rings. “We also hope that it inspires other review platforms to take a firmer stance against reduced solicitation and incentivisation,” she says.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/yelp-has-a-wall-of-shame-for-businesses-caught-paying-for-fake-reviews-110011882.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/yelp-has-a-wall-of-shame-for-businesses-caught-paying-for-fake-reviews-110011882.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> c98aff66-e442-4a70-a617-7bbf74c71ba7</guid><dc:creator> Karissa Bell</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 20 Sep 2023 11:00:11 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1695162052</ingested><modified> 2023-09-19T22:20:57+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Karissa Bell]]></category><media:content height="3388" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-images/2020-06/89f90150-aaa3-11ea-a775-76af53faa836" width="5000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3388" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-images/2020-06/89f90150-aaa3-11ea-a775-76af53faa836" width="5000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[SOPA Images via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[UKRAINE - 2020/04/07: In this photo illustration a Yelp logo seen displayed on a smartphone. (Photo Illustration by Igor Golovniov/SOPA Images/LightRocket via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[In this photo illustration a Yelp logo seen displayed on a...]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Nikon's Zf full-frame camera puts speed and video power in a retro body]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Nikon has unveiled its latest full-frame camera, the 24.5-megapixel Zf with retro style and technology borrowed from the company&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nikons-z8-mirrorless-camera-offers-8k60p-raw-video-and-20fps-burst-speeds-141556946.html">high-end Z8</a> and <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nikon-z-9-mirrorless-camera-review-143006924.html">Z9 cameras</a> . With a new sensor and processor, it promises powerful features like 14-fps max shooting speeds, advanced AI autofocus and 4K 60p video. At the same time, it&#39;s a highly manual camera with a lot of old-school touches and multiple colorways, all designed to touch that vintage-loving nerve.</p><p> The body and handling emphasizes manual controls, with no less than five dials on top to control shooting mode, video/photo/B&amp;W, aperture, shutter speed and exposure compensation. It also has a pair of shooting dials front and back and a D-pad style controller, but no joystick. The &quot;grip&quot; is just a small ridge. With all that, the Zf really does look like a an old school Nikon film camera — right down to the chrome-plated shutter release button. </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/dbaf5020-5794-11ee-beeb-5bcacaa65a23" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/dbaf5020-5794-11ee-beeb-5bcacaa65a23" style="height:1713px;width:2400px;" alt="尼康 Zf 在复古包装中兼具速度和视频功能" data-uuid="2edf4cab-ae10-35db-996c-1e80133b7fed"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Nikon</div></figure><p> The Zf&#39;s magnesium-alloy body is smallish, but not very light at 710 grams (Sony&#39;s A7 IV is 659 grams). It does offer &quot;high dust- and drip-resistance&quot; though, Nikon says.</p><p> The high-resolution 2.1-million-dot vari-angle touch display fully articulates for vlogging and selfies, while allowing touch function controls and focus point selection. For astro shooters, it has a &quot;Starlight view mode&quot; that boosts display brightness in dark scenes. Meanwhile, the OLED viewfinder has a decent 3.68-million dot resolution and 0.8 times magnification.</p><p> It has two card slots, but with a serious caveat. One is a high-speed UHS-II card slot, but the other is a UHS-I microSD slot — the only model with that combo as far as I know. The battery is a weak point, offering only 380 shots on a charge, compared to 580 for the Sony A7 IV. Other features include a USB 3.2 Gen1 port with charging support, mic/headphone ports and a micro HDMI connector. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/eeac7540-5794-11ee-befe-f3f937d9cc52" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/eeac7540-5794-11ee-befe-f3f937d9cc52" style="height:1600px;width:2400px;" alt="尼康 Zf 在复古包装中兼具速度和视频功能" data-uuid="10f2ec5d-3922-368f-84d3-260e10806372"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> DIXIE_DIXON2022 for Nikon</div></figure><p> Inside, it has a backside-illuminated (BSI) 24.5-megapixel sensor and Expeed 7 processor borrowed from the high-end Z models. That gives it autofocus powers akin to the Z8, including Nikon&#39;s 3-D tracking plus AI-powered subject detection that can find people, dogs, cats, birds, cars, motorcycles, bicycles, trains and planes. It&#39;ll even detect far-away faces that take up as little as 3 percent of the frame&#39;s longest side.</p><p> As for image quality, the standard ISO range of 100 to 64,000 promises good low-light capability, and it has a pixel shifting mode that boosts resolution up to 96-megapixels for static scenes. In line with the retro styling, Nikon has a dedicated black &amp; white mode (with its own dial setting), that enables multiple monochromatic settings ranging from flat to high-contrast &quot;Deep Tone Monochrome.&quot;</p><p> It can hit 11fps shooting speeds in RAW mode (14fps with JPEGs) in electronic shutter mode (Nikon doesn&#39;t list specs for mechanical shutter) and offers a reduced-quality 30fps JPEG-only mode with a pre-burst option to ensure you won&#39;t miss a shot. The five-axis IBS (or vibration reduction, as Nikon calls it) reduces shake by up to 8 stops with a supported lens. Stabilization can be linked to the focus point, rather than just the center of the image as with most systems. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/c098cdc0-5794-11ee-9e3f-3dab27eb4110" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/c098cdc0-5794-11ee-9e3f-3dab27eb4110" style="height:1642px;width:2400px;" alt="尼康 Zf 在复古包装中兼具速度和视频功能" data-uuid="8b2149db-c525-3726-b56f-b60c4c8b4f73"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Nikon</div></figure><p> On the video side, the Zf can record full-frame 4K at 30p from a supersampled 6K image, or 4K60p with a DX (1.5 times) crop, along with 1080p/120p. Video can be captured with 10-bit H.265 recording, which will give users better color fidelity and more options in post. However, H.265 files require a powerful computer, meaning you might have to convert them to another format for editing.</p><p> Based on the specs, the Nikon Zf looks like a solid camera that can compete against models like Panasonic&#39;s S5 II and Sony&#39;s A7 IV. However, it sets itself apart from those models based on its retro styling and manual controls, which should appeal to a certain segment of buyers. The Nikon Zf arrives in October 2023 at a competitive $2,000 price for the body only, or $2,240 with the retro-styled Nikkor Z40 f/2.0 SE lens. If you want one of the other colors (Indigo Blue, Sepia Brown, Bordeaux Red, Sunset Orange, Moss Green, StoneGray), you&#39;ll pay $2,100 for the body only. </p><div id="78cca4d629374a14b6bff471aaf36927"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/nlPai8y6SvY?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no" data-embed-domain="www.youtube.com"></iframe></div><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/nikons-zf-full-frame-camera-puts-speed-and-video-power-in-a-retro-body-092033908.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/nikons-zf-full-frame-camera-puts-speed-and-video-power-in-a-retro-body-092033908.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 6520e729-c153-4678-ab54-18f7343398a6</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 20 Sep 2023 09:20:33 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1695204997</ingested><modified> 2023-09-20T10:16:44+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Cameras & Photography]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="1600" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/9c90d410-5788-11ee-bbf9-de327b1bea99" width="2400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1600" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/9c90d410-5788-11ee-bbf9-de327b1bea99" width="2400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[DIXIE_DIXON2022 for Nikon]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Nikon's Zf has speed and video power in a retro package]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Nikon's Zf has speed and video power in a retro package]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Max will offer free live sports streaming until March 2024]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Max 透露，它正在为订阅者提供免费观看体育赛事直播的机会——无论如何，时间有限——证实了<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/max-may-offer-live-sports-at-no-extra-cost-for-several-months-141015332.html"><em>彭博社</em>之前有关该服务的报道</a>。以前称为 HBO Max 的流媒体服务将于 10 月 5 日推出 Bleacher Report (B/R) 体育附加套餐。观众可以通过该服务观看华纳兄弟探索频道线性网络上直播的所有体育赛事，包括 NBA、 MLB、NCAA、NHL 和美国足球比赛。该附加组件恰逢 MLB 国家联盟分区系列赛、常规 NHL 赛季和 NBA 开幕之夜推出。</p><p>在 2024 年 2 月 29 日之前，美国的订阅者将可以免费享受该附加服务，无论他们是支付有广告支持的会员选项还是无广告会员选项。之后，他们必须开始每月支付 10 美元的访问费用。<em>彭博社</em>在报告中表示，该公司讨论了利用“疯狂三月”大学篮球锦标赛作为新产品的卖点。锦标赛在促销期结束后不久开始，并且可能足以吸引粉丝为附加内容付费至少几个月，因为它将于四月结束。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>除了现场比赛报道外，体育附加节目还让观众可以观看 WBD 的所有赛前和赛后直播节目。他们还可以观看视频点播内容，包括 Bleacher Report 的精彩集锦、体育纪录片以及以体育名人和运动员为主角的视频广播。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/max-will-offer-free-live-sports-streaming-until-march-2024-074445038.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/max-will-offer-free-live-sports-streaming-until-march-2024-074445038.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 28de3883-e2b7-474a-a796-5124910c0649</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 20 Sep 2023 07:44:45 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1695195863</ingested><modified> 2023-09-20T07:44:27+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Sports & Recreation]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="4000" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/c0435ff0-5782-11ee-bfef-2c10c9c98f2e" width="6000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="4000" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/c0435ff0-5782-11ee-bfef-2c10c9c98f2e" width="6000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[New Orleans Pelicans guard CJ McCollum (3) and San Antonio Spurs guard Devonte' Graham (4) in the first half of an NBA basketball game in New Orleans, Tuesday, March 21, 2023. (AP Photo/Tyler Kaufman)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Spurs Pelicans Basketball]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Terraria developer Re-Logic is giving $100,000 to two open-source game engines amid Unity debacle]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Unity 决定在每次安装使用其游戏引擎的游戏时<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/unity-will-start-charging-developers-each-time-their-game-is-installed-214851801.html">开始收取费用，</a>这引起了愤怒并引发了集体诉讼，这是可以理解的。为了回应 Unity 投下的炸弹，<em>泰拉瑞亚</em>开发商 Re-Logic 已介入推广和支持开发人员可以使用的替代开源游戏引擎。在 X（该网站前身为 Twitter）上的一篇帖子中，Re-Logic 称 Unity 的举动是“掠夺性的”，并“明确谴责”拟议的费用调整，以及“实施这些调整的方式不正当”。</p><p>这位开发者继续说道：“Unity 多年来培​​养的信任被轻率地抛弃，转而以另一种方式压榨发行商、工作室和游戏玩家，这是最悲伤的部分。” Re-Logic 表示，简单的公开声明是不够的，因此它向开源游戏引擎 Godot 和 FNA 各捐赠 10 万美元。它还将继续支持这两个项目，今后每月为每个项目提供 1,000 美元。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="630bebd3bb8c4e90ae82cc369ffafd87"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="zxx" dir="ltr"> <a href="https://t.co/ZqzGMTui0f">pic.twitter.com/ZqzGMTui0f</a></p> — 泰拉瑞亚🌳 (@Terraria_Logic) <a href="https://twitter.com/Terraria_Logic/status/1704227519027651016?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 9 月 19 日</a></blockquote></div><p><em>《泰拉瑞亚》</em>取得了巨大成功，并成为多年来跨平台最畅销的视频游戏之一。虽然 Re-Logic 可以承担这样的捐赠，但这不是公司的责任——而且社区根据其公告收到的积极回应数量知道这一点。</p><p> Unity 首次推出了新的“运行时费用”，计划于一周前的 2024 年 1 月 1 日实施。费用将根据开发商使用的计划而有所不同。例如，Unity Personal 和 Unity Plus 订阅者在过去 12 个月的收入和 200,000 次终身安装中达到 200,000 美元后，将为每次安装支付 20 美分。然而，在最初宣布几天后，Unity <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/unity-apologizes-and-promises-to-change-its-controversial-game-install-fee-policy-082408455.html">收回了承诺</a>并承诺更改该政策。它还解释说，订阅服务的所有者（例如涉及 Game Pass 的微软）将必须支付费用，而不是开发商本身。目前，Unity 运行时费用的具体细节仍不清楚，但它承诺很快就会发布更新。 </p><div id="266c718014214d1faf68257a8fef9e96"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">我们已经听到你的声音了。对于周二宣布的运行时间收费政策给您带来的混乱和焦虑，我们深表歉意。我们正在倾听、与我们的团队成员、社区、客户和合作伙伴交谈，并将对政策进行更改。我们将在几个小时内分享更新……</p> - Unity (@unity) <a href="https://twitter.com/unity/status/1703547752205218265?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 9 月 17 日</a></blockquote></div><p></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/terraria-developer-re-logic-is-giving-100000-to-two-open-source-game-engines-amid-unity-debacle-054307544 .html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/terraria-developer-re-logic-is-giving-100000-to-two-open-source-game-engines-amid-unity-debacle-054307544.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> e9db2b47-728d-4008-bce8-e24bf7de7ed8</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 20 Sep 2023 05:43:07 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1695188564</ingested><modified> 2023-09-20T05:42:48+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="3576" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-images/2020-04/1f5606c0-83cc-11ea-a7d1-b81a19d19a5a" width="5277"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3576" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-images/2020-04/1f5606c0-83cc-11ea-a7d1-b81a19d19a5a" width="5277"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[La Bicicleta Vermella via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Boy with headphones playing on his computer]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Xbox head Phil Spencer responds to a day of massive leaks]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>经过一天的泄露，包括<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/huge-leak-reveals-microsoft-will-launch-an-all-digital-xbox-series-x-and-new-gyro-controller-090442796.html">全数字 Xbox Series X</a> 、高级控制器、 <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/leaked-microsoft-documents-detail-cloud-hybrid-next-gen-xbox-for-2028-110309102.html">“云混合”控制台</a>、毫无结果的<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/xbox-chief-phil-spencer-believed-a-nintendo-merger-would-have-been-his-career-moment-114525963.html">任天堂收购计划</a>以及一些关于<em>博德之门 3 的</em><a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.polygon.com/23880311/microsoft-baldurs-gate-xbox-series-x-version">非常刻薄的言论</a>， <em>&nbsp;</em> Xbox 负责人 Phil Spencer 首次公开（半私下）谈论了这一情况。</p><p>在 X 上，斯宾塞说：“很难看到我们团队的工作以这种方式共享，因为已经发生了很多变化，现在和未来都有很多值得兴奋的事情。”他补充说，该公司“将在我们准备好时分享真正的计划”。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="757bb5cc1cac48bbb5ce37490b69fd4f"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">我们已经看到了围绕旧电子邮件和文档的对话。很难看到我们团队的工作以这种方式共享，因为已经发生了很多变化，现在和未来都有很多值得兴奋的事情。当我们准备好时，我们将分享真正的计划。</p> — 菲尔·斯宾塞 (@XboxP3) <a href="https://twitter.com/XboxP3/status/1704233222752571842?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 9 月 19 日</a></blockquote></div><p>在发给微软游戏部门员工并由<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/19/23881174/microsoft-xbox-leak-gaming-phil-spencer-memo"><em>The Verge</em></a>完整发布的一份内部备忘录中，斯宾塞走得更远。完整的注释如下：</p><div class="breakout-box"><blockquote><p>团队，</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>今天，在法庭诉讼中提交的几份与我们拟议收购动视暴雪有关的文件无意中被披露。我知道这令人失望，即使许多文件已经存在一年多了，而且我们的计划已经发生了变化。</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>我还知道我们都非常重视我们计划和合作伙伴信息的保密性。这次泄漏显然没有达到我们的期望。我们将从所发生的事情中吸取教训，并更好地前进。我们都在工作中投入了令人难以置信的热情和精力，但这并不是我们希望与社区分享辛勤工作的方式。也就是说，还有很多值得兴奋的事情，当我们准备好时，我们将与我们的玩家分享真正的计划。</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>最后，我感谢你们为 Xbox 团队所做的所有工作，为我们的玩家带来惊喜和喜悦。在未来的几天和几周内，让我们继续专注于我们可以控制的事情：继续《Starfield》的惊人成功，即将推出令人难以置信且易于使用的《极限竞速》，并继续构建数百万玩家可以享受的游戏、服务和设备。</p></blockquote><blockquote><p>菲尔</p></blockquote></div><p>毫无疑问，对于 Xbox 的每个人来说，这都是漫长的一天。斯宾塞在这两封信中都尽力淡化泄露文件的重要性，暗示 Xbox 的硬件计划自 2022 年首次内部共享以来已经发生了变化。原始幻灯片概述了推出无盘、圆柱形 2TB 版本的计划2024 年的 Xbox Series X，以及具有“精确触觉反馈”（如 PlayStation 的 DualSense）和直接到云功能（如 Stadia 的控制器）的更新控制器。展望更远的未来，这些文件包括第 10 代 Xbox 游戏机的计划，重点是“云混合游戏”，预计将于 2028 年发布。</p><p>此外，斯宾塞显然曾经一度想收购任天堂（但微软似乎最终选择了动视暴雪，这就是我们最终陷入这一漏洞的原因）。我们<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/everything-we-learned-from-the-biggest-leak-in-xbox-history-161027198.html">在这里</a>汇总了今天文档转储中的所有新闻。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/xbox-head-phil-spencer-responds-to-a-day-of-massive-leaks-220326175.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/xbox-head-phil-spencer-responds-to-a-day-of-massive-leaks-220326175.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 0a44923a-4b67-4876-a84d-e208ac6222c4</guid><dc:creator>杰西卡·康迪特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 19 Sep 2023 22:03:26 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1695212542</ingested><modified> 2023-09-20T12:22:25+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jessica Conditt]]></category><media:content height="1688" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/32980bf0-57b0-11ee-bd55-9d9ae3f1313d" width="3000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1688" medium="image" url="h